 St Francis Bay - The Kouga Local Municipality has advised residents and businesses in St Francis Bay that electricity supply to the whole of St Francis Bay will be interrupted this Thursday. The electricity interruption will be from 8am to 3pm. "The shutdown is necessary for emergency repair work," the municipality said. "Our sincere apologies for any inconvenience this may cause." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 